ny is only one part of a much larger toolkit of Socratic humor, the broader intellectual context of which must be better understood if we are to appropriate Socratic thought for our own modern ends.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGreek wit and humorxPhilosophy. 0aGreek wit and humorxPolitical aspects. 0aIronyxPolitical aspects. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096491440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964914423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964914/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles